verbose_text: Adipogenesis is commonly induced by growing preadipocyte cells such as OP9 or 3T3-L1 cells to confluency and then applying an adipogenic mixture consisting of insulin, fetal bovine serum (FBS), dexamethasone (dex), which is a synthetic glucocorticoid, and 3-isobutyl-1-methylxanthine (IBMX), which is an inhibitor of phosphodiesterase that increases cAMP levels.
